                <head>225. Editorial Note</head>
                <p>At 4 p.m. on January 30, President <persName corresp="#p_EDD1"
                        >Eisenhower</persName>, Secretary <persName corresp="#p_DJF1"
                        >Dulles</persName>, Prime Minister <persName corresp="#p_ESA1"
                        >Eden</persName>, Foreign Secretary <persName corresp="#p_LSJSB1"
                        >Lloyd</persName>, and their advisers met and again discussed Middle Eastern
                    issues. For text of the discussion of the Arab-Israeli dispute, see volume XV,
                    pages 108–109. For text of the discussion of the Baghdad Pact, see volume XII,
                    pages 243–244. For text of the discussion of Saudi Arabia and Buraimi, see
                    volume XIII, pages 329–334.</p>
                <p>The memorandum of conversation was given restricted circulation to appropriate
                    U.S. officials on February 7 as ETW <gloss target="#t_MC1">MC</gloss>–2.
                    (Department of State, Conference Files: Lot 62 D 181, CF 648)</p>
            </div>
